{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs1foJ2hoGrPWS3dduBP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TLS is now enabled and verified:\n\n**What was done:**\n- Generated a CA, a node cert (SANs covering `crdb-cluster`/`crdb-cluster-public` headless & public service DNS names, wildcard `*.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`, each pod's explicit DNS name, `localhost`, `127.0.0.1`), and a client `root` cert using `openssl` (the `openssl-toolbox` pod referenced in the task didn't actually exist in the cluster, so certs were generated with `openssl` directly and loaded straight into the Secret — same result).\n- Stored `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, `node.key`, `client.root.crt`, `client.root.key` in Secret `crdb-cluster-certs` (cockroachdb namespace).\n- Updated the `crdb-cluster` StatefulSet: replaced `--insecure` with `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, mounted the secret at that path (`defaultMode: 0600`), and switched the liveness/readiness probes to `HTTPS`.\n\n**Gotcha hit and fixed:** StatefulSet rolling updates apply one pod at a time (highest ordinal first) regardless of `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`. That briefly put `crdb-cluster-2` on TLS while `-0`/`-1` were still insecure — incompatible transports, so the cluster lost quorum. Fixed by deleting all 3 pods at once so they recreated together against the already-updated (TLS) pod spec.\n\n**Verified:**\n1. `--insecure` is rejected: `ERROR: node is running secure mode, SSL connection required`.\n2. `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs` succeeds: `SELECT 1` returns `1`.\n3. `cockroach node status --certs-dir=...` shows all 3 nodes live and available, confirming the cert served by the nodes is the one from `crdb-cluster-certs`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":623,"cache_read_input_tokens":84390,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_in